Statistics South Africa  publishes
fourth-quarter gross domestic product data at 11:30 a.m. in  Pretoria . Economic growth probably accelerated to an annualized
4.2 percent in the final three months of last year from 2.6
percent in the third quarter, according to the median estimate
of 21 economists surveyed by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alastair Reed in Johannesburg at 
